      "text": [
        " وَ لا تُصَعِّرْ خَدَّكَ لِلنَّاسِ قَالَ لِيَكُنِ النَّاسُ عِنْدَكَ فِي الْعِلْمِ سَوَاءً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Al Barq, from his father, from Abdullah Bin Al Mugheira and Muhammad Bin Sinan, from Talha Bin Zayd, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding this Verse <span class=\"ibTxt\"><a href=\"/#/books/quran:31#h18\"><a href=\"/books/quran:31#h18\">[31:18]</a></a> And do not turn your cheek away from people in contempt</span>. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘For the people to happen to be equal with you regarding the knowledge’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          " 2. A number of our people has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad al-Barqi from his father from ‘Abdullah ibn Mughirah and Muhammad ibn Sinan from Talha ibn Zayd from abu ‘Abdallah (a.s.) about this verse. “Do not scornfully turn your face away from people. .” <a href=\"/#/books/quran:31#h18\"><a href=\"/books/quran:31#h18\">[31:18]</a></a> ‘so that people would all be equal in matters of knowledge.’”"
        ]
      }
